  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education Through Sports for 400 girls in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stop inequality in education, we want Tanzanian girls to school. They are oppressed and hardly graduate from secondary schools. Through sports, health and life-skills education, 13 to 19 years old girls learn health and life-skills, increasing their self-awareness &amp; confidence, academic performance, reduce teenage pregnancies and raise awareness of their rights. Influential community members and traditional initiation leaders are mobilized to improve girl friendliness in communities.</narrative>
  </description>
